1
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:11,250
OK

2
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:15,600
Thanks.

3
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:33,300
Could you help me?

4
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,299
Did Marius gave you this fish bowl, like this?

5
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:54,300
There are other fish.

6
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:56,299
What a weird picture.

7
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,299
Listen, can you ask Daniela to feed them while we're away?

8
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:01,300
They're just fish. Nothing can happen if they are not fed a couple of days.

9
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:13,300
Did you take the toothpaste?

10
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:17,300
Yes, and some cotton absorbent too. You'll get another.

11
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:23,300
-Do you have some soap left? -Check in the drawer.

12
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:25,299
-There is no more.

13
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:27,299
-I'll get it for you. I'll be out for cigarettes anyway.

14
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:31,300
-Get some Amo or Lux. No more Palmolive, I got dandruff because of it.

15
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:38,300
-Could you go to Petronela and get my hairdryer?

16
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:40,299
-You're packing as if you're mountain tripping.

17
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:43,300
-Do you have any money left?

18
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:47,300
-Check the jeans. It's a wallet in the back pocket.

19
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,299
-That's where you keep your money, in a wallet?

20
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:52,300
-Better than hanging out of the pockets like you're used to.

21
00:02:56,300 --> 00:03:00,300
-Close the damn door. It's windy.

22
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:07,300
-Did you see Petronela? -She was in the shower earlier.

23
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,299
-Hot water? -Yup

24
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:20,300
-Petronela? -Not in here.

25
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,299
-Otilia? -Yea.

26
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:26,300
-What is it?

27
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:30,300
-The teacher noticed you were not around on Thursday.

28
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:34,300
-Didn't I ask you to bail me out?

29
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:35,299
-I tried. But she said she heard that one two weeks ago.

30
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:39,300
-She said you'd better bring a waiver. -I will

31
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:46,300
-Does she smoke? - Vikent.

32
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:59,300
-It's open.

33
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:04,300
-Morning. Did you start already?

34
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:07,300
-It's Wednesday. With the lecturer.

35
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:11,300
-'The thorn birds' with Richard Chamberlain. Tonight if you want.

36
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,299
-How is Gabi? -She's depilating.

37
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:17,300
-I want an Assos and a Kent. -Don't have Kent.

38
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:21,300
-Where can I find some? - You can't, I got some Marlboro instead.

39
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:25,300
- What am I to do with it? Give me an Assos and a Lux.

40
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:39,300
-Anything else? -A Tic-tac. An orange one.

41
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:45,300
-The tic-tac is on me. -Thanks.

42
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:49,300
-If you change your mind, you're welcome tonight. Ramona is coming too.

43
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:53,300
-Not really.

44
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:02,300
-They're so cute. Are they yours?

45
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:05,300
-No, I found them yesterday near the power station. Do you want one?

46
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:08,300
-I can't. Gabitza is allergic to cats.

47
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:10,299
-What do you feed them? - Some dumplings yesterday night.

48
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:14,300
- I'll get some powder milk for them. - Thanks.

49
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:18,300
-Hey girls. Tell Gabi her father phoned and said he'll be here tomorrow around 10.

50
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:25,300
-I'll tell her. -Thanks.

51
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:30,300
-Your father called. He'll be here. -Damn.

52
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:35,300
-Did you tell your parents? -Tell them what?

53
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:39,300
-He's supposed to be here at 10.

54
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:45,299
-I can't figure out what to do about this exam.

55
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:47,299
- You'll take it another day.

56
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:50,300
-Should I take some notes to read?

57
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:54,300
-No point to do that.

58
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:03,300
-Didn't you have some powder milk? -It's in the Nescafe can.

59
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:28,300
-How much do I owe you? -80.

60
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:32,300
-Here is the powder milk.

61
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:35,299
-Is it a girl? -Yup.

62
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:37,299
-How much is rexona? - 50

63
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:41,300
- Do you have Kent? -No, ask Radu.

64
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:44,300
-And the blister? -25.

65
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:45,299
-Progesterol. Is it good?

66
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,299
-German, made in Hungary under license.

67
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:49,299
-How come you know?

68
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:53,300
-My cousin told me. She uses them, not me.  I'm too fat anyway

69
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:57,299
-Expensive. Do you find any buyers?

70
00:06:57,300 --> 00:07:01,300
-No doubt about it. Instantly.

71
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:05,300
-I'm leaving. I have to dye my hair. Red head

72
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:08,300
-Really? -Kidding, actually I put on nut concoction cause my hair is thinning

73
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:11,300
-Hey, can you tell Petronela to bring the hair dryer?

74
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:13,299
-She's taking an exam. I'll bring it later.

75
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:17,300
-Bye, good luck. -Bye

76
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:28,300
-When are you going to meet Adi? -At 11.

77
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:38,300
-I think I have fever. -Take an aspirin.

78
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,299
-I think it's my bad tooth. I need painkillers. Vial painkillers.

79
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:44,300
-Check the kit. Maybe there is some left.

80
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:53,299
-What a bad timing. I have an appointment at the dentist.

81
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:56,300
-No time for that.

82
00:07:56,300 --> 00:08:00,300
-Can I ask you something? -Say it.

83
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:03,299
-Could you deal with the money part? You know I am not even able to bribe a ticket collector.

84
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:07,300
-I'll deal with it.

85
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,299
-Here is the money, count it.-2700, right?

86
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:20,300
-Yes.

87
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:27,299
-My stomach aches. -Eat something.

88
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:30,300
- Eat what? I can't eat anything.

89
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:34,300
-Don't worry. Everything will be all right.

90
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:40,300
-Come on, enough. Bye

91
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:46,300
-Don't turn back. It bodes bad. -I forgot the address.

92
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:50,300
-Stop being superstitious. You're not from the country side.

93
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,299
-You know something, I'll bring some notes with me after all.

94
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:56,300
-Then bring them.

95
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:36,300
-Tickets please! Let me see your tickets please.

96
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,299
-Do you have a spare ticket? - No.

97
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:52,300
-Tickets please

98
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:46,300
-Excuse me. Did Ady get in?

99
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:57,299
-What are you doing? Learning?

100
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:58,299
-Perusing those abstracts.

101
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,300
-Did anyone get in?

102
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:05,300
-It started late. They couldn't find the key to the classroom.

103
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:11,299
-Stop. Your classmates can see us.

104
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:15,300
-So what? - I'm embarrassed.

105
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:18,299
-Listen, Diana asked if we wanted to swap the trips.

106
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:20,299
-So that she goes to Izvor and we go to Costinesti.

107
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:24,300
-The same timetable? -Not really.

108
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:26,299
- 7-14 Izvor, 15-22 Costinesti,

109
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:30,300
-I have the last exam on the sixth.

110
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:32,299
-Then I'll have to go home for a week and then return.

111
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:36,300
-I don't know, it's rather complicated.

112
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:41,300
-You did remember about the money, didn't you? -Yea, sure.

113
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:44,299
- You give it  to me in an envelope or what?

114
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:48,300
- I wanted to keep it separated from the money for the flowers.

115
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:56,300
- 300, right? - I'll give it back when I get my scholarship.

116
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:58,299
- Are you hungry? Do you want me to get you something?

117
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,299
- My mother packed some cookies for me.

118
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:02,299
-She woke up in the morning to make cookies for you?

119
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:06,300
-She woke up to prepare the meringue cake, cause after 8 the gas pressure drops.

120
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:09,300
- Please get the flowers for my mother. I think I'll be stranded here all day.

121
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:13,300
- I don't think I...  can make it.

122
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:22,300
- Where...?  Are you telling me you won't be able to attend my mother's birthday?

123
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:30,300
- Don't be angry with me. - I am. She's making your favorite cake and you don't come?

124
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:33,299
- You told her to make it for me? -I did, and she made the cake.

125
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:36,300
- It's just that I can't, not that I don't want to.

126
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:40,300
- What do you mean you can't? What is it you have to do? Say it.

127
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:45,300
- I can't tell you now. You can't tell me now?

128
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:49,300
-Don't you trust me? Say it if you don't.

129
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:52,300
- It's not about that. I just don't understand why you can't come. Do you keep secrets from me?

130
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,299
- I have no secrets. I'll tell you later, that's all.

131
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:57,300
- Why is it such an issue?

132
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:03,300
- Ok, if you don't find it an issue, I don't know what else to say.

133
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:06,299
- If I had to come to your place for the first time and I had forgotten about it, that would have been an issue.

134
00:13:06,300 --> 00:13:10,300
- Come on, I don't want to argue with you.

135
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:15,300
- Who started it? I asked to get some flowers for my mother and you say you don't want to come.

136
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:19,300
- Fine, I'll come. I 'll find a way and I'll make it.

137
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,299
- You're making me a favor now. - Hey, will you stop? do you want me to come or not?

138
00:13:23,300 --> 00:13:27,300
- The professor would like you to speak a little lower, ok?

139
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:35,300
- What kind of flowers do you want? - Don't take  anything.

140
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:40,300
- Tell me. Do you want carnations?

141
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:46,300
- Get some gladiolas. - How many?

142
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:48,299
- 48. - I can't, they're even.

143
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:52,300
- Then how many? - Don't know. 49 maybe.

144
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:58,300
- She'll say I don't her age if I get 49.

145
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:02,300
- Who's counting, anyway? - You don't know my mother.

146
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:07,300
- Get 47 then. I don't know. Do as you please. I'll just take how many you want.

147
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:09,300
- Ok, I'll manage one way or another and I'll come.

148
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:12,300
- Listen, we won't get too formal, are we?

149
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:21,300
- No, you'll come good and proper. At 5.

150
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:25,300
No delays

151
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,299
- You're starting to annoy me. I'm never late.

152
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:32,300
- Unless something unforeseen pops up, in which case everybody is late.

153
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:34,299
- Ady, do you your report card with you? They won't allow us without it. - Yes

154
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:37,300
- I'm leaving.

155
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:40,300
-  What's the time? - Past twenty. Do you need mine?

156
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:41,299
- No, no , keep it.

157
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:44,300
- See you later.

158
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:48,300
- Don't you kiss me? - No, cause you've upset me

159
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:55,299
- Don't upset me anymore. - You too.

160
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:59,300
- Bye. - Bye.

161
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:05,299
- How can I get a pack of Kent cigarettes?

162
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:09,300
- Why didn't you tell me. I would have brought it for you.

163
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:13,300
- I need it for Gabi. Go to Unirea, you'll find some black marketers.

164
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:17,300
- Bye.

165
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:31,299
- Hello.

166
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,299
- I'm listening.

167
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:37,300
- I have a booking. On the name Dragut.

168
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,299
- You have a booking here. Since when?

169
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:40,299
- Today. Tonight, I mean.

170
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:42,299
- What I want to know is when did you made it?.

171
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:46,300
- Since last Tuesday.

172
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:55,300
- There is nothing here.

173
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:58,299
- A friend of mine made it. I know for sure it was Monday, or Tuesday.

174
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:01,300
- Do you know who did she talked to?

175
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:04,300
- No, but I 've heard she gave her name and address.

176
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:05,299
- What was the name again?

177
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:09,300
- Dragut.

178
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:19,300
- Nope. There is no Dragut in here.

179
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:25,300
- Listen, go find Nelu for me.

180
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,299
- Maybe my colleague knows you.

181
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,300
- I told you it wasn't me who booked the room.

182
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:33,299
- My friend called and a man answered.

183
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:37,300
- On the phone. So she didn't come here personally?

184
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:38,299
- I don't know exactly. I guess she called.

185
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:42,300
- Anyone can call.

186
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,299
- Was the reservation confirmed? Yesterday?

187
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:49,300
- What to confirm it for?

188
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:52,300
- I would really like you to talk in a civilized manner.

189
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:54,299
- The reservation has to be confirmed at least 24 hours prior.

190
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:55,299
- The man she talk to didn't mention anything like this.

191
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:59,300
- I doubt he didn't.

192
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:05,300
- Nelu....

193
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:09,300
No... It hurts.

194
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,299
There is someone here who says you've booked a room for her yesterday.

195
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:14,299
- Not yesterday, Tuesday.

196
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:17,300
- Or Tuesday.

197
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:20,300
- Ok, What was the name again?

198
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:21,299
- Dragut.

199
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:25,300
- Dragut(Nice), ha, that's the name all right.

200
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:27,299
- Yea, thanks.

201
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:30,300
- Listen, could you call me if they send the pay check?

202
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:34,300
- Ok, fine.

203
00:17:36,300 --> 00:17:39,300
- No, if the reservation had been made I would have find it.

204
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:40,299
- So, what do we do now?

205
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:44,300
- Do what now?

206
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:45,299
- Is anyone serving in the shop?

207
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,299
- In a minute.

208
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:51,300
- We really need a room. Please, let's tackle this

209
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,299
- Tackle what miss? There is a delegation from Bucharest who arrived yesterday. The whole place is full.

210
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,299
- Do you understand?

211
00:17:56,300 --> 00:18:00,300
- Anything. I don't mind if it has 3 beds.

212
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:04,300
- Can't you understand Romanian? It seems you don't.

213
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:11,299
- Do you have Kent?

214
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:15,300
- 80, a pack.

215
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:54,300
- We have a delegation on the way. See what you can do.

216
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:59,300
- Ok, I can't talk anymore. I call you back. Bye, bye.

217
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:05,300
- I'm listening.

218
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:09,300
- Hello. I'd like a room starting tonight.

219
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:10,299
- Tonight?

220
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:12,299
- Yes, please.

221
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:14,299
- Everything is taken.

222
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:16,299
- I don't mind if it has 3 beds.

223
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:20,300
- Can you call Marcu here, please.

224
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:24,300
- How many nights?

225
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:28,300
- Two, but it could take longer.

226
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:34,300
- Today... not really.

227
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:38,300
We have a room but starting tomorrow

228
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:39,299
- But we really need it tonight, please.

229
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:42,300
- How many? - Two.

230
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:46,300
- With double bed. - Doesn't matter.

231
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:52,300
- Yes? - Go to the bar and get two coffees to that table.

232
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:54,299
- Is it neckezol or ness?

233
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:58,300
- Just go. She knows what to give you.

234
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:02,300
Tell her it's for me.

235
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:04,300
- I can't spell the name, Miha...  - Mihatescu with a T.

236
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:09,300
- So, can you help me?

237
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:11,299
- I don't really know. He hasn't confirmed the reservation until now, but still...

238
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:15,300
- Please, I'm begging you.

239
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:21,299
- It's a double bed, did I tell you?

240
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:24,300
- It's ok.

241
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:28,300
- Do you have an ID?

242
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:31,299
- You have a temporary address here. Are you a student?

243
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:33,299
